HEADWORD: Chautauqua system
<hw>Chau*tau"qua sys"tem</hw> (of education) <pr>(?)</pr>. <def>The
system of home study established in connection with the summer schools
assembled at Chautauqua, N. Y., by the Methodist Episcopal bishop,
<person>J. H. Vincent</person>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Chauvinism</ent>⟦br⟧
